<h1>High national defence spending</h1>
<p class="lede">This scenario illustrates how the national escape clause for defence interacts with the net-expenditure rule and the control account.</p>

<h2>Setup</h2>
<p>The scenario assumes a Member State invoking the national escape clause, with defence-related expenditure rising substantially over the plan horizon. Use the <strong>Load defence scenario</strong> button in <em>Step 3 — Enter plan</em> of the FISCO workbook to populate the relevant cells.</p>

<h2>What FISCO shows</h2>
<p>The scenario walks through how the additional defence spending is treated relative to the net-expenditure aggregate, how the cumulative balance of the control account responds, and how the assessment surfaces compliance vs. non-compliance against the Code of Conduct (ECOFIN 16230/25).</p>

